        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 5:55PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles northeast of Lincoln, or 38 miles west of Cascade, moving east
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bowmans Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
